          <br>
          <h5> Cooking instructions for Hyderabadi Chicken Biryani </h5>
          <ul>
            <li>
                  Mix 3Kg chicken pieces with 1 kg Hyderabadi Biryani Gravy and 1kg yogurt. Keep aside for 45 minutes.
            </li>

            <li>
                  Heat 100gms ghee in a pan and add contents of the spice pack (supplied separately with this pack of gravy).Add marinated chicken pieces and 2.5 Kg water.
            </li>

            <li>
                    Cook for 10 to 15 minutes on medium heat till tender and gravy thickens.
            </li>

            <li>
                    Cook 1250gm basmati rice in water separately.
            </li>

            <li>
                    Take cooked Rice qty 2500 Gms and make layers of Rice and cooked chicken. 
                 
            </li>

            <li>
                 
                    Pour saffron and milk mix and pure ghee 20 Gms.
                 
            </li>

            <li>
                 
                    Give Dum to the Biryani. 
                 
            </li>

            <li>
                 
                    Garnish with Fresh chopped coriander and Fried onions.
                 
            </li>

          </ul>

          <h5> Cooking instructions for Hyderabadi Mutton Biryani</h5>
