            </li>

          </ul>


          
          <h5>  Cooking instructions for Vegetable Hyderabadi Biryani</h5>
          <ul>
            <li>
               
                  Heat 80gms ghee in a pan and add contents of the spice pack (supplied separately with this pack of gravy).
               
            </li>

            <li>
                 
                  Add to this 2500g chopped mixed vegetables (such as French beans, carrots, cauliflower, potatoes and green peas), entire content of 1 kg Hyderabadi Biryani Gravy  and 2500 kg water.
                 
            </li>

            <li>
                 
                    Cook for 10 to 15 minutes on medium heat .
                 
            </li>

            <li>
                 
                    Add 400Gms yoghurt and simmer for another 2 minutes on medium heat.
                 
            </li>

            <li>
                 
                    Add some chopped coriander and mint leaves.
                 
            </li>

            <li>
                 
                    Cook 1250gm basmati rice in water separately.Take cooked Rice qty 2500 Gms and make layers of Rice and cooked vegetables.
                 
